text: Aaron Muss (born December 15, 1994) is an American snowboarder. He competed in the 2013 and 2017 FIS Snowboard World Championships, and in the 2018 Winter Olympics, in parallel giant slalom. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:American male snowboarders Category:Olympic snowboarders of the United States Category:Snowboarders at the 2018 Winter Olympics
